cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper deals with word embeddings, which are widely used in natural language processing (NLP) tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also presents a framework for analyzing structures in the semantic vector space, which involves deep neural networks, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. Additionally, the paper proposes a method for solving NLP problems, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the word analogy task, which is related to information retrieval (IR), making cs.IR another possible category. Finally, the paper uses sub-vectors to decompose word embeddings, which is a technique that can be applied to neural networks, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) another possible category.
